1. -- { Arvid Ivanovich Kubbel (1889-1938) was arrested after sending his chess compositions to a German chess magazine, bypassing the USSR Chess Section's Central Composition Committee, which had to approve all compositions for publication. Charged under Article 58 1a (treason) he was sentenced to 10 years of hard labor, and was executed on January 11, 1938, en route to a Siberian prison camp.

---

There really is not much to say in this introduction. Hopefully you have read all of the items in the other preface, but this one contains more 'nice to know' and 'now I understand where you're coming from' information that is not essential to the course.

So if you wish to skip this chapter, then feel free to do so - that's pretty much it. } *

