6. d4 {[%cal Ge7e5,Bc2c4,Bb1c3]} ( { Black's Knight is no longer pinned to the King, the Queen is protecting the Knight, and there is pressure from Black on the d-file, so that all needs to be taken into account. We now have an exception to our plan. If we were to play } 6.b3 { then Black could follow with } 6...e5 { . Ignoring the threat and blindly playing } 7.Bb2 { results in } 7...e4 8.h3 Bxf3 9.gxf3 { giving Black a nice advantage. } ) ( { Addressing } 6.b3 e5 { with } 7.Ba3 { sees } 7...Qh6 8.Bxf8 e4 9.Bxc6 exf3 10.Rxf3 bxc6 11.Bc5 Nf6 { and Black is in no hurry to win the exchange. } ) ( { Taking the pawn via } 6.b3 e5 7.fxe5 { is worse, as } 7...Nxe5 8.Be2 Bxf3 9.Bxf3 Nf6 { and Black is in charge.

