The most common responses by club players, and those covered in this course, are: } { 2...d5 40.5% }{ 2...b6 10.6% }{ 2...Nf6 7.9% }{ 2...Be7 7.5% }{ 2...Nc6 6.2% }{ 2...Bc5 5.0% }{ 2...d6 4.9% }{ 2...c5 4.1% } { d5 transposes to positions in the previous chapter.

Of course, it is important to be aware of the various possibilities, but we can see that the likelihood of encountering a position that does not include an early d5 drops quickly. If you are not comfortable and competent with the moves from the previous chapter then I would recommend returning to it until that is the case, as those are the most likely lines you will encounter.

While I allowed very few soft fails in the previous chapter, this and the next chapter I have been very generous, taking Stockfish 15 out to a depth of 30 and allowing all moves that show less than half a pawn valuation from the recommended move. That is because being exact is much less important than having the general ideas down. } )
