{ Now that we have the first six moves under our belt, it is time to look at what happens from there.

The truth of the matter is that for club players, both sides playing prepared moves beyond the 6th move is not exactly a regular thing. The stronger one gets, the further into the game that preparation becomes.

The 56 variations that have been learned so far follow the moves that Black is most likely to make. In October 2022 the positions following White's 6th move in these 56 variations were comprised of 42,292 games - some positions were found in thousands of games, others as few as 2 or 3.

As we are trying to learn a repertoire that we will most likely be facing, it makes little sense to work on continuations for those that exist in only a handful of games, and much more sense to be familiar with those in the thousands.

Just assuming that your games will follow to your 6th move in a variation that has been covered, the idea here is to continue from where we left off, in the order that you are likely to actually see that position. In this first continuation chapter we will look at 13 variations that have more than a 5% chance of being seeing.

I decided not to name each variation in this chapter similar to the variation that got us here, which is why the titles are simply a number followed by a letter. The number is in the order of the likelihood of seeing the position, and the letter just allows for variations from the same starting point to be identified. This breaks the inertia one might have from learning a line, and will force one to think in terms of piece placement.

One caveat is that I have not looked through all 42,280 games - some of them, but not close to the total. Some of the positions we are starting from may not necessarily have arrived from the players working through Bird's Opening, and may be transpositions from completely different openings. This means that the ordering may not be exact. I think that it is close enough, but if you are willing to go through all of the games and weed out those that came about through an opening that we are not studying so that the count can be exact, please do not let me know.

I will note that winning percentage, from this point on, will be less meaningful because the number of games played in a particular position may not be significant. It will still be used to help us select the best move, but will be weighted less than it was during the first six moves. } 1. -- *

