9. Ne5 {[%cal Bf1f3]} { While we have the opportunity, we step into a temporary outpost poking into Black's territory. We have also made the f3 square available in case we with to do a Rook lift. } Qc7 
10. d3 {[%cal Bb2g7][%csl Ge4]} { This is very much a multi-purpose move, and one that will be seen on a regular basis. It stops Black from considering moving their Knight to e4, as well as opening a slot for the queenside Knight to develop. This keeps that nice diagonal open for the Bishop. It also assists in keeping the diagonal open in case Black tries to move a pawn forward to try to close down the diagonal.

