{ This is a continuation of 2... Nf6 3... e6 with 4... Be7 and 5... O-O [/variation/21430223]. } 6... c5 { This is a well-traveled position, as it is a transposition from the Classical Variation of the Nimzo-Larsen Attack. } 
7. O-O Nc6 
8. Ne5 {[%mdl 32768]} {[%cal Bd1e1]} ( 8.e1 { has a better win percentage, but not only is } { Ne5 a better move, it has a more forcing continuation that leads to a nice position. } ) Qc7 { Qc7 is a bit better than taking the newly placed Knight. } 
9. c4 {[%cal Be5c6]} ( 9.Nxc6 { is also a good move, though the few games in the database say that White has a very poor record playing that. } ) d4 
10. Nxc6 {[%cal Be3d4]} ( 10.exd4 { is another good choice. White wins most of the 8 games in the database, but those few games lack significance. } )-- ( { Black does not want to take back with the Queen, as 10...Qxc6 11.exd4 cxd4 12.Bxd4 Rd8 13.Bf3 Qe8 14.Be3 and White is simply in charge. }{ Taking with the pawn, the less intuitive move, equalizes, 10...bxc6 11.exd4 and Black does not need to take back immediately 11...Bd6 , which has never been found, results in 12.dxc5 Bxf4 13.Kh1 White is fine here and the game is equal.

