The variations here are offered in the order of the number of games that exist in the Lichess database currently in the final position (I did not include the lines that resulted in no games in the database) .

As was the case with the first review, I suggest that you have the moves of the previous chapters down solidly. If you have the ability to identify your Difficult Moves then I recommend that you get them down to a low number. If you have difficulties with a particular move then as stated above, there will be links to the relevant variations. If you are confident then you can pause the variations on which the line has been built so that they do not show up in your reviews.

Just a reminder - you may have seen '(P)' following some variation names in the first three chapters and the two 'Continuations' chapters. These indicate variations that you may wish to pause. That is because the two 'Review' chapters include these variations, so by pausing them and including the variations from the Review chapters within your reviews, you will remove that redundancy. Personally, I tend to get overwhelmed by the number of items in my reviews, so this is a way of reducing that number. On the other hand, you may decide to retain them, as the idea of redundancy in the positions you are most likely to see may be beneficial. Regardless, you've got the choice to do what works best for you. } *

