[FEN "rnbq1rk1/1pp1bpnp/p2pp1p1/4P2P/3P1P2/2NB1N2/PPP3P1/R1BQK2R w KQ - 0 1"]

1. hxg6 { This is a continuation from 7B [/variation/22967827]. It really does not have much to do with the Greek Gift, but shows that the threat can be equally deadly regardless.

In this particular position there is one game in the database, so we will use the next move from there before deviating. } { We will look at taking back with the f-pawn in a moment, as was played in the game, but we will first look at the much worse } { 10...hxg6 We learn that it is generally best to take toward the center in these situations, but this move is just disaster. With a Rook on h1 this is just opening the door to a loss. 11.g4 works toward shattering Black's kingside protection. 11...Nd7 12.f5 Black is destined to lose a piece. } { 10...fxg6 is the correct response for Black. In the game White played Ne4, which is a fine move, but busting down the door is the idea here with 11.g4 Black tries to get a piece into the game with 11...Nc6 but 12.Qd2 Nb4 13.f5 is just too much. } *

[Event "The Classical Bird for Club Players"]
[White "Where Did They Go From Here?"]
[Black "7C"]
