{ Black has just taken our Knight on c4. Retaking is the correct choice but there are three ways to do that. One retains our small advantage, one equalizes the position, and one gives Black a nice advantage.

Identify all three and which is which. } 1. dxc4 ( { First off, } 1.Nxc4 { which results in } 1...dxc3 2.Ba3 Bd4 { and White has got a set of problems to deal with, so that is the worst choice. } )-- ( { Best is to go against the instinct to take toward the middle with dxc4 followed by 1...Bxe5 2.fxe5 O-O 3.cxd4 cxd4 4.Qxd4 and White retains their small advantage. The advanced extra pawn can be used to disturb Black's pawn structure and Black still needs to figure out where to put their undeveloped Knight. }{ 1.bxc4 is not as good, since 1...Bxe5 2.fxe5 Qxe5 3.cxd4 cxd4 4.Qa4 O-O 5.Qxc6 Rb8 and there is really no advantage for either side. } )
