{ This is from a game between Henry Bird and Joseph Blackburne in 1892. Bird lost the entire advantage with his move choice and went on to lose the game - the second best move 'only' loses a two and a half pawn evaluation.

What is the best move in this position? } 1. e4 -- ( { The game could have continued } 1...Bg4 2.Bg5 Qe8 3.O-O-O Rb8 4.Qd5+ Be6 5.Qa5 { with a nice advantage. } { Unfortunately for Bird, 1.Qb3+ was a blunder, and after 1...Kh8 2.Bg5 Qe8 his position fell apart. } { The second best move is 1.Bg5 but after 1...Qe8 2.O-O-O Kh8 Black has mitigated much of White's advantage. } )
