---

}-- ( 1...Bh6 { retains Black's small advantage following } 2.Rfe1 { though after finding the fork it is so difficult to back off. } { If Black insists on taking the Rook 1...Nxf1 then 2.Nxf4 Nxh2 3.Kxh2 and White has a nice advantage. } { Other moves by White just do not work, for instance 1.Qe1 forgets about 1...Nxc2 and @@StartFEN@@1rbq1rk1/2pp1ppp/p1p1p3/4P3/3P1b2/1P2nN2/PBP1N1PP/R2Q1RK1 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@ 1.Qb1 which would be the second best move runs into 1...Nxf1 (actually, Bh6 is a better move, but who would be able to resist not taking the Rook?) 2.Nxf4 Ne3 3.c4 Nf5 and White's pieces are scattered. } )
