{ This one is different because it involves more than just a single move, so spend some time to try to figure out the continuations. It is a rich position that is more complicated than may initially appear. } 1. h3 {[%mdl 32768]} { If you got this move then you can declare victory and walk away. However, if you wish you can continue to see how many of the six additional moves in the sequence you can get. } e5 ( { Black cannot drop the Knight back to } 1...Nh6 { as } 2.Qxf6 Rg8 3.Rae1 { so it attacks White's Queen. } ) 
2. Qd3 { Taking the pawn removes much of White's advantage: } { 1.fxe5 Nxe5 2.Qf2 Nxf3+ 3.Qxf3 so the Queen goes to its only square. } Qc5+ { Black can drop the Knight back at this point } { 1...Nh6 but at the cost of opening things up 2.fxe5 fxe5 3.Ng5 O-O-O 4.Be3 - { 4.Ne6 simply loses the Knight. } 
3. Kh1 h5 ( { Black can try to trade Queens at this point } 3...Qc4 { but that is not in our best interest } 4.Qc2 O-O-O 5.hxg4 { and bringing the Knight back at this time } { 4...Nh6 does not help as 5.fxe5 f5 6.b3 is worse for Black. } ) ( { A quick glance at } 3...Nf2+ { might give one the impressions that there is advantage to gaining the exchange via } 4.Rxf2 Qxf2 { but that is illusory. If one continues the line then it can be seen that Black has invited disaster: } 5.fxe5 fxe5 6.dxc6 bxc6 7.Be3 { - attacking the Queen, but more importantly getting out of the way for the Rook } 7...Qxb2 8.Rd1 { Now White has to play } 8...Be7 { or } { 8...c5 or 8...Ba3 in an attempt to forestall the inevitable, which might present itself in the form of 8...Be7 9.Bxb6 O-O 10.Bc7 } ) 
4. fxe5 { Opening the f-file. } Qc4 ( { Attempting to trade Queens makes the most sense. Hoping to save the Knight by trading it off only opens the f-file to allow an attack } 4...Nxe5 5.Nxe5 fxe5 6.Rac1 ) ( 4...Nf2+ { might still appear appealing, but again does not work in pretty much the same way as a move ago } 5.Rxf2 Qxf2 6.dxc6 Rh7 7.exf6 Rd8 8.Nd5 ) 
5. Qc2 { Trading is not in our best interest. } Nxe5 { Eventually Black needs to allow the f-file to open up. } 
6. Nxe5 fxe5 
7. Bg5 ( 7.b3 { also works. Interesting position with a lot of possibility. } ) *

