{ Black has infiltrated this closed position with an advantage. There is one move that can keep the game close, all others lose for White. } 1. Rf2 -- ( { With Rf2 the infiltration is temporary. Black will need to play very accurately to maintain the advantage. } 1...Nc6 { opens the b8-g3 diagonal to prevent Black's Queen from being trapped. It also allows White to play } 2.Rf3 Qd6 { (or the Queen could go to e5 or c7) and Black has a one pawn advantage. } { In the game White played 1.Nf3 , the second best move, but one that gives Black a 5 pawn advantage. As if to drive home the point that even a 2450 player does not necessarily make the best moves, Black cut their 5.7 pawn advantage almost in half by playing 1...Qxh3 instead of the more prudent Bd6. Black eventually went on the win the game in 51 moves. } )
